#### Key Concepts

1. Students demonstrate their problem solving abilities by applying problem solving to a new context. 

#### Common Difficulties

The last lesson was about a graph problem as well. However the Minimal Spanning Tree is different than this problem often referred to as the Hamiltonian Path Problem (similar to the Traveling Salesman Problem). Students will need to look carefully for those differences as they go through the problem solving process.  The biggests difference if that you not just creating a tree between the set of nodes but a path that touches every node once. 

